Patent Application

Title: Method and System for Issuing Community Tax Certificates and Other Permits and Clearances as Digital Certificates

Applicant:

Abstract:
The present invention relates to a method and system for issuing community tax certificates and other permits and clearances as digital certificates. The invention is a novel and non-obvious way of using verifiable credentials, digital wallets on a blockchain as payment provision, and machine learning to improve the efficiency and transparency of the permit and certificate issuance process.

Claims:

1. A method of issuing a digital certificate for a community tax certificate comprising:
a. receiving an application for a community tax certificate from a taxpayer;
b. verifying the identity of the taxpayer using verifiable credentials;
c. determining the eligibility of the taxpayer for a community tax certificate based on the application;
d. generating a digital certificate for the community tax certificate, wherein the digital certificate includes a unique identifier, an expiration date, and a digital signature;
e. storing the digital certificate on a blockchain;
f. receiving an electronic payment for the community tax certificate using a digital wallet on the blockchain; and
g. notifying the taxpayer that the community tax certificate has been issued.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein the verifiable credentials comprise at least one of the following:
i. a government-issued identification card;
ii. a passport;
iii. a driver's license;
iv. a birth certificate;
v. a utility bill;
vi. a bank statement; and
vii. a credit card statement.
3. The method of claim 1, wherein the blockchain is a public blockchain or a private blockchain.
4. The method of claim 1, wherein the digital certificate is generated using a machine learning algorithm that learns from past community tax certificate applications to improve the accuracy of the eligibility determination.
5. The method of claim 1, wherein the eligibility determination is based on at least one of the following:
i. residency in a particular community;
ii. ownership of a particular property;
iii. payment of a particular tax;
iv. compliance with a particular set of regulations; and
v. fulfillment of a particular set of requirements.
6. A system for issuing a digital certificate for a community tax certificate comprising:
a. a processor;
b. a memory;
c. a tangible non-transitory computer-readable medium storing instructions that, when executed by the processor, cause the system to:
i. receive an application for a community tax certificate from a taxpayer;
ii. verify the identity of the taxpayer using verifiable credentials;
iii. determine the eligibility of the taxpayer for a community tax certificate based on the application;
iv. generate a digital certificate for the community tax certificate, wherein the digital certificate includes a unique identifier, an expiration date, and a digital signature;
v. store the digital certificate on a blockchain;
vi. receive an electronic payment for the community tax certificate using a digital wallet on the blockchain; and
vii. notify the taxpayer that the community tax certificate has been issued.
7. The system of claim 6, wherein the verifiable credentials comprise at least one of the following:
i. a government-issued identification card;
ii. a passport;
iii. a driver's license;
iv. a birth certificate;
v. a utility bill;
vi. a bank statement; and
vii. a credit card statement.
8. The system of claim 6, wherein the blockchain is a public blockchain or a private blockchain.
9. The system of claim 6, wherein the digital certificate is generated using a machine learning algorithm that learns from past community tax certificate applications to improve the accuracy of the eligibility determination.
10. The system of claim 6, wherein the eligibility determination is based on at least one of the following:
i. residency in a particular community;
ii. ownership of a particular property;
iii. payment of a particular tax;
iv. compliance with a particular set of regulations; and
v. fulfillment of a particular set of requirements.
